    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.01/808a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in the American Republics
                            Except Argentina and Bolivia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 3, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>If you consider it advisable, please inform the Foreign Minister of the country
                    to which you are accredited that at his press conference today when asked to
                    comment on reports from Cuba that the other American Republics are preparing to
                    recognize Bolivia soon, the Secretary stated: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have not information to that effect. The governments thus far have
                            been proceeding as a unit in that respect and their action has been
                            based primarily on considerations of carrying on the war in support of
                            the Allied cause.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
